findings.recommended_fix:
Strengthen the text to reflect the AMC, for example:

"Possession of a Part‑66 AML or national qualification alone does not entitle a person to certifying staff or support staff authorisation. The organisation assesses and confirms that each candidate:
- has adequate knowledge, skills and experience for the specific aircraft type/group or component configuration maintained;
- understands the applicable operator and organisation procedures (e.g. technical log, MEL, component handling, independent inspections);
- demonstrates an appropriate safety attitude and adherence to procedures.
These aspects are verified through training records and a documented competency assessment prior to authorisation."

Introduce a clear one‑off authorisation procedure, for example:

"One‑Off Certification Authorisations (Unforeseen Cases)
- In unforeseen situations as per 145.A.30(j)(5), a one‑off authorisation may be issued only under the responsibility of the Compliance Monitoring Manager (CMM) after an individual assessment of the case.
- Prior to issuing such an authorisation, the CMM ensures that:
  • full technical details of the required work are established and communicated to the certifying staff;
  • an approved procedure exists for coordinating and controlling all maintenance activity at the location under the one‑off authorisation;
  • the person receives all necessary maintenance data and special instructions, and a detailed step‑by‑step worksheet is prepared and provided;
  • the person holds equivalent authorisations on aircraft of similar technology, construction and systems, and has sufficient knowledge and experience for the task.
- The holder signs off each step on the worksheet; completed tasks are verified and recorded with the one‑off authorisation reference. All one‑off authorisations are logged and reviewed by the CMM."
